		             [11,	5,	1,	'Ministry of Governmental Services',	'Office Building',	'This is a broad, three-story concrete building with several large skylights but few windows. The lobby has a curved glass facade with a soaring roof that stands in contrast to the simplicity of the rest of the building.',	'A large, skylit lobby contains rows of public service counters for various social or legalitarian services, some of which are cordoned off and appear to have been disused for some time. The rest of the building consists of large, open workspaces with few private offices.'],
		             [11,	6,	1,	'King\'s Island Medical Clinic',	'Hospital',	'This is a broad seven-story building of aged brick and carved stone, with cast-iron windows and sheets of verdant ivy that grow partway up the walls.',	'The halls of this building are painted in flaking pastel paint. The patient rooms are cramped and aging, and most are divided into shared rooms by curtains. One wing ends in a small but ornate chapel whose stained-glass windows are devoid of specific religious symbols.'],
