		             [14,	5,	1,	'Ministry of International Affairs and Trade',	'Office Building',	'This is a four-story building of very new red brick with multiple wings. It has high windows and several small domes.',	'The lobby floor is a world map of Meropis in polished and multicolored stone, with the location of Laurentia indicated by a gold star. Most of the first floor is dedicated to press conference rooms and meeting rooms flanked with Laurentian flags, and many of the offices in the upper floors appear to have been occupied but rarely used.'],
		             [14,	6,	1,	'Parlamentum Laurentum',	'Parliament',	'This neo-baroque building is where the Parliament of Laurentia met. All of the windows are broken and some are scorched by fire, but the dome retains a brilliant bright blue luster and gold trim.',	'The Legislative Council of Laurentia met in this wing of the building. Numerous chairs are scattered about the entrance to the meeting hall, having apparently been used in a barricade at some point.'],
		             [14,	7,	1,	'Parlamentum Laurentum',	'Parliament',	'This neo-baroque building is where the Parliament of Laurentia met. All of the windows are broken and some are scorched by fire, but the dome retains a brilliant bright blue luster and gold trim.',	'Ornate frescoes decorate the walls in the main hallway, and the central rotunda depicts the first century of Laurentian history, from the settlement of the region to the construction of this capitol.'],
		             [14,	8,	1,	'Parlamentum Laurentum',	'Parliament',	'This neo-baroque building is where the Parliament of Laurentia met. All of the windows are broken and some are scorched by fire, but the dome retains a brilliant bright blue luster and gold trim.',	'The Laurentian House of Assembly met in this wing of the building. Now the halls are filled with scattered papers, and the enormous meeting hall has been ransacked.'],
		             [14,	9,	1,	'Library of Parliament',	'Library',	'This three-story granite building is built in imitation of the neo-Baroque style of Parliament, though it was clearly constructed much more recently. A few of the small windows that line the ground floor have been broken.',	'Most of the library is filled with densely packed archives that were once accessed via an automated system that no longer functions. The third floor contains a large, spacious reading room with excellent views of the Inner Harbor.'],
		             [14,	10,	1,	'The Queen\'s Finest',	'Restaurant',	'The building appears to be a restaurant, constructed fairly recently. Despite appearing to be closed, the aroma of freshly-cooked food wafts from the entrance of the building.',	'Several tables and chairs are placed about the place and there is a large kitchen in the back. The wall facing Parliament is covered in a black-and-white print of the view of the island as it would have appeared in the 1920s.'],
