		             [22,	21,	1,	'Connolly General Hospital',	'Hospital',	'This ten-story structure consists of a jumble of interconnected buildings made of grey concrete panels, though all appear to have been built at the same time. Signs directing visitors to the emergency room and other departments are the most colorful sights present.',	'The interior of the hospital is difficult to navigate and consists of several wings, some of which have clearly been renovated more recently than others. The air is stale and smells of harsh hand cleaning agents. A faint beeping noise can sometimes be heard, but no source of the sound is evident.'],
